  "body": "I noticed in the eth_getTransactionReceipt the status field is returning wrong value for some transactions, I noticed it is returning \"0\" indicating a revert for many transactions that were actually successful (\"1\")\r\n\r\nYou can reproduce it by getting the receipt from many public node providers, for this example I choose a random tx \"0x60ed161964624fb79abff5e3ae968f0b48c47a2f2898dbc8207dbd625f4b6e15\":\r\n\r\n`curl https://mainnet.infura.io/v3/<key> \\\r\n    -X POST \\\r\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\r\n    -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getTransactionReceipt\",\"params\": [\"0x60ed161964624fb79abff5e3ae968f0b48c47a2f2898dbc8207dbd625f4b6e15\"],\"id\":1}' | jq`\r\n\r\nInfura returns: \"status\": \"0x1\"\r\n\r\n`curl http://api.archivenode.io/<key>/erigon \\\r\n    -X POST \\\r\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\r\n    -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getTransactionReceipt\",\"params\": [\"0x60ed161964624fb79abff5e3ae968f0b48c47a2f2898dbc8207dbd625f4b6e15\"],\"id\":1}' | jq`\r\n\r\nArchivenode.io pinned to erigon returns: \"status\": 0, like my personal erigon node.\r\n\r\n`curl https://eth-mainnet.alchemyapi.io/v2/<key> \\\r\n    -X POST \\\r\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\r\n    -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getTransactionReceipt\",\"params\": [\"0x60ed161964624fb79abff5e3ae968f0b48c47a2f2898dbc8207dbd625f4b6e15\"],\"id\":1}' | jq`\r\n\r\nAlchemy returns: \"status\": \"0x1\"\r\n\r\nEtherscan returns success, which corresponds to \"status\": \"0x1\"\r\n\r\nI'm using the v2021.06.05 tag.",
